# Sandbox r+w redirect or disable env meant for agent sessions ONLY.
#
# NOTE: Additions/Changes to this requires rebuild of the devcontainer for it to be picked-up
#
# Primary use is configuring tools to either:
# 1. Disable r+w to locked down dirs (e.g. `/etc`, etc.)
# 2. Redirect r+w to dedicated, sandboxed dirs (i.e. `NONO_SANDBOX_DIR`, `NONO_SANDBOX_TMPDIR`)
#
# Sourced at runtime by the `claude` alias in `.devcontainer/Dockerfile`, inside a
# subshell so the vars stay scoped to the sandboxed process and never leaked into
# into the interactive shell.
#
# WHY: the nono sandbox has strict r+w constraints on both `$HOME` and `/tmp` where
# many tools read and write to, resulting in EACCES errors.
#
# FORMAT:
# - one VAR=value per line
# - the following ENV variables will be made available:
#   - `NONO_SANDBOX_DIR` - more permanent sandbox dir that surives container spin-down
#   - `NONO_SANDBOX_TMPDIR` - more ephemeral sandbox dir that may not survive container spin-down
# - commented and blank lines are ignored

# Stops git from reading system-level `/etc/gitconfig` which `nono` locks down
GIT_CONFIG_NOSYSTEM=1

# Supports tools like docker-compose that reads + writes tmp files in `/tmp`
# - e.g. docker-compose: https://github.com/docker/compose/issues/4137
TMPDIR=${NONO_SANDBOX_TMPDIR}
